title: For Sale:  Awesome Sig Sauer Personal Defense Wepon-Carbine Platform
postcontent:
Alright we all know how hard it is to find a personal defense weapon right now especially when you need some extras features and plenty of available rounds to last. Everyone has their own opinion and I feel like what I have here is a very practical, personal defense weapon.

What I have is a brand new Sig Sauer P250 9mm mounted into a Enhanced Sig Sauer Adaptive Carbine Platform (ACP). The ACP is a great building block with rails in the 6, 9, & 12 oclock position which are compatiable almost any tactical accessory of your choice. There is already a brand new Sig Sauer STS-081 Red Dot Sight installed.

I was going to add the STL-300J for the fore grip with flashlight/strobe light and laser. Get some high capacity mags and I think that this would make this a really mean looking and functionable tactical weapon that would be great in a close quarter combat. I think that they also offer a folding stock and that most noise suppressors with fit this platform. 

Some say this setup is heavy, just carry a pistol instead but this setup is more accurate, ready for combat plus its really no more heavy than any other PDW with all the needed accessories and ammo during an emergency. I own a few weapons including an AR which I think is great but if you cant find one, they are too expensive, or they get banned then this setup is a great alternative as it can offer the same tactical features as other Personal Defense Weapons. 

Also what I think is important is during a real world life emergency is available ammo, 9mm ammo is much more readily available right now and if/when other defense weapon ammo can not be found this could bail you out. I know that I have more 9mm ammo than anything else and if I was in a pinch Im sure that someone would be more likely to help me if I needed some more.

This is a great, brand new setup that has never been fired, if youre interested in seeing one in action check out the Sig video by going to this link: http://www.sigsauer.com/Catalog/acp-adaptive-carbine-platform.aspx

title: For Sale:  Walther P99 9mm
postcontent:
Very good condition Walther P 99 9mm double action semi auto pistol. It's gun features a titanium coated finish, double stack magazine, ambidextrous mag release for right or left handed shooters. Adjustable back steps for different size hands, adjustable sights, removable front sight inserts. Is gun comes with 2-10 rd mags but they do make hicap 15 rd mags that are available. This gun originally sold for over $900 when it was first introduced in the 90's. included is original case. There is some signs of wear that can be seen on the slide in the photo. 

If interested please call REDACTED. Florida residents only. 


The Walther P99 is a short recoil-operated locked breech semi-automatic pistol that uses a modified Browning cam-lock system adapted from the Hi-Power pistol. The P99 has a glassfiber-reinforced polymer frame and steel slide assembly. It can be broken down into its main parts or field stripped with a take down catch without the help of tools.
It uses an internal striker as opposed to an external hammer, with a red-painted striker tip that protrudes from rear of the slide when the gun is cocked, as well as a loaded chamber indicator on the right side of the slide.
The original first generation P99 had a traditional Double-Action/Single-Action trigger with a decocker. When the slide is racked completely to the rear upon loading, the trigger remains in the forward position for the first shot and the Double-Action mode is activated. The trigger travel is 14 mm (0.55 in) long in the Double-Action mode at approximately 35 N (7.9 lbf) trigger pull. On all subsequent shots, the trigger travel is reduced to 5 mm (0.2 in) at 20 N (4.5 lbf) trigger pull. For manually deactivating the Single-Action mode without loading the pistol the P99 features a key or knob on the slide. The Double-Action mode can also be manually activated by moving the slide approximately 10 mm (0.4 in) back.[8] Currently the original trigger is no longer offered and has been replaced by 3 trigger variants.
The striker protrudes visibly and palpably from the back of the slide when the firearm is in a constant partially cocked state. It should however be noted that the striker of the second generation P99QA variant does not protrude from the back of the slide, unless fired, as the firearm is in a constant partially cocked state.
Ergonomics were a key focus in the design of the firearm, and as a result, three interchangeable grip backstraps are included (small, medium and large) to accommodate various hand shapes and sizes; this feature permits most shooters a comfortable and efficient grip on the firearm. This adaptable grip was innovative at the time the P99 was introduced.
The slide and other metal parts of the pistol are Tenifer treated (a nitriding process also used on Glock pistols). The Tenifer finish is between 0.04 mm (0.002 in) and 0.05 mm (0.002 in) in thickness, and is characterized by extreme resistance to wear and corrosion; it penetrates the metal, and treated parts have similar properties even below the surface to a certain depth.[9] The Tenifer process produces a matte gray-colored, non-glare surface with a 64 Rockwell C hardness rating and a 99% resistance to salt water corrosion (which meets or exceeds stainless steel specifications),[10] making the P99 particularly suitable for individuals carrying the pistol concealed as the highly chloride-resistant finish allows the pistol to better endure the effects of perspiration.[9]
The P99 features four internal safeties, iron sights adjustable for both windage and elevation, tool-less take down, and an ambidextrous magazine release incorporated into the trigger guard. The lower forward edge of the frame also known as the dust cover has a mounting-bracket or rail interface system for attaching accessories, such as a tactical light or laser sight.
